<h3 id="adding-editing-and-deleting-plant">6. Adding, editing and deleting plant</h3>
<p>
    In order for plant to be available for hire in the system, a record of it all must be stored
    somewhere. For each plant the original purchase price of it, the rate at which it is hired out
    and the status and condition is all recorded in PIMS.
</p>
<h4 id="add-new-plant">6.1. Add new plant</h4>
<p>Here's a working example of how to add a new plant:</p>
<ol>
    <li>On the main menu, click <strong>Stock</strong> &raquo; <strong>Plant</strong>.</li>
    <li>Just below the main menu, click <strong>Create New</strong>.</li>
    <li>
        Fill in each of the blank boxes next to each label. Here's what each of them mean:
        <table class="table display table-striped order-column table-responsive table-help-guide">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Label</th>
                    <th>Example</th>
                    <th>Description</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td class="help-guide-term">id</td>
                    <td>Tprism18</td>
                    <td>
                        This is an identifier for a plant; a short code. This isn't automatically
                        assigned, so you'll need to come up with the ID yourself. It should be unique.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="help-guide-term">new id</td>
                    <td>55025</td>
                    <td>
                        This is another identifier for the plant. Some plant have old identifier codes
                        and a process is in place for them to be assigned new identifiers. Use this
                        for the new plant id if an old plant id already exists, otherwise make this
                        the same as the id above.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="help-guide-term">description</td>
                    <td>Prism</td>
                    <td>
                        Use a relatively short name of the plant that best describes what it is.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="help-guide-term">when purchased</td>
                    <td>1/03/2006</td>
                    <td>
                        The date when the plant was purchased.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="help-guide-term">when disused</td>
                    <td></td>
                    <td>
                        The date when the plant was retired from use. Leave this empty if the plant
                        is still in use otherwise it will not show in the list of available items
                        when checking out that plant to a job.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="help-guide-term">default rate</td>
                    <td>0.50</td>
                    <td>
                        The default charge out rate for hire. It is a default because individual
                        transactions can have their rate altered which will not affect this rate.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="help-guide-term">cost</td>
                    <td>150.00</td>
                    <td>
                        The purchase price of the plant.
                    </td>
